concept_explanation.palindrome_check:
**Check if string is palindrome — two approaches:**

```java
// O(n) time, O(1) space — two pointers
bool isPalindrome(String s) {
    int lo=0, hi=s.length()-1;
    while(lo<hi) {
        if(s.charAt(lo)!=s.charAt(hi)) return false;
        lo++; hi--;
    }
    return true;
}

// O(n) but O(n) space — reverse comparison
bool isPalindromeAlt(String s) {
    return s.equals(new StringBuilder(s).reverse().toString());
}
```

concept_explanation.expand_around_center:
**Expand Around Center — O(n) for each center, O(n²) total:**

```java
// For each center (n odd + n-1 even = 2n-1 centers total):
for(int center=0; center<n; center++) {
    // Odd length palindromes (single center char):
    int lo=center, hi=center;
    while(lo>=0 && hi<n && s.charAt(lo)==s.charAt(hi)) {lo--;hi++;}
    // lo+1 to hi-1 is the palindrome
    if(hi-lo-1 > maxLen) { maxLen=hi-lo-1; start=lo+1; }
    // Even length palindromes (center between chars i and i+1):
    lo=center; hi=center+1;
    while(lo>=0 && hi<n && s.charAt(lo)==s.charAt(hi)) {lo--;hi++;}
    if(hi-lo-1 > maxLen) { maxLen=hi-lo-1; start=lo+1; }
}
```
